title: AP Micro Exam study guide[PDF]
description:
Microeconomics/Macroeconomics is a comprehensive book on economics for students appearing for the Advanced Placement exams. The book comprises of chapters on economic systems, demand and supply, theory of consumer choice or behavior, costs, production and supply, product markets, perfect competition, monopoly, inflation and unemployment, fiscal policy, and international trade and exchange. In addition, the book consists of two full-length sample tests for thorough revision and final practice. This book is essential for students aspiring to pursue their higher education in economics from American Universities.

About the Authors

Frank W. Musgrave was a professor of economics at Ithaca College for 42 years. He was also the co-owner of The Edge of Thyme Bed and Breakfast in Candor. Frank was a part of the Oxford University Round Table and was a DANA Professor Recipient.
